Roam Research CLI (Go)

Usage:
  roam-cli [command]

Daily Use:
  get         Get page by title, block by uid, or daily page by date
  help        Help about any command or topic
  journal     Get journaling blocks from Daily Notes
  move        Move a block to a page or section
  save        Save GFM markdown as a Roam page or daily page section
  search      Search blocks or pages by terms
  status      Check roam-cli credential and API connectivity status

Low-level API:
  batch       Low-level batch actions API
  block       Low-level block APIs
  q           Execute raw datalog query

Flags:
  -h, --help      help for roam-cli
  -v, --version   version for roam-cli

Use "roam-cli [command] --help" for more information about a command.

HELP TOPICS
  configuration       How to set up credentials and connection options for roam-cli.
  datalog             Roam Research exposes a Datomic-flavored Datalog query API with Clojure built-in functions.
  exit-codes          Stable exit codes for scripting and automation.
  format              How `save` converts GitHub Flavored Markdown (GFM) into Roam blocks.
  read-examples       Examples for reading pages, blocks, daily notes, and searching.
  workflow-examples   Common daily workflows and multi-step patterns.
  write-examples      Examples for saving GFM markdown and creating content.
  writing-guide       Choose the right command for writing content to Roam Research.

Use "roam-cli help <topic>" for more information about a topic.
